comment_data.body:
Consider adding a brief documentation comment for this function to explain its purpose and behavior, particularly that it blocks autocommands during cleanup and handles cases where the buffer cannot be wiped. This would improve code maintainability.
```suggestion

/// Clean up the dummy FileType buffer created by do_ft_buf().
/// Autocommands are blocked during cleanup, and if the buffer cannot be
/// wiped (for example, if it is still displayed or current) its dummy
/// flag is cleared so it is kept instead.
```

